title: For Sale:  Colt 1863 Arizona Centennial -- .22 LR Frontier Scout Revolver, Cased - C&R OK
location: south dakota, North Dakota, United States
postcontent:
What a handsome little Commemorative Colt has assembled here! The black frame is nicely set off by the gold plating of the detail parts. This is a looker, not a shooter, although there is nothing wrong with the 2nd Generation Frontier Scout pistols! This is handsomely presented in an attractive presentation case, commemorating a state where Free Men Remain Free! (said the Californian...) 


The top of the barrel is stamped, “Colts PT FA. MFG. Co. Hartford CT. U.S.A.” The left side of the barrel is stamped and gold filled, “1863 - Arizona Territorial Centennial - 1963” The left side of the frame has the Rampant Colt logo. The right side of the barrel is marked, “Colt Single Action Frontier Scout .22 LR”. There is some engraving on the heel of the butt.   The gun is mounted with a fixed front blade, and a notch rear sight. 

The grips are white pearl-like material, starting to yellow a bit from age. The correct Colt medallion is on each panel. There is a bit of rubbing from the presentation case lining but otherwise almost no wear. The grips rate in about Excellent overall condition.    The gun is finished in an attractive black finish, which is accented with a gold cylinder, grip housing, hammer, trigger, ejector button, cylinder base pin, and screws. 

This gun retains about 99% of its metal finish. There is a bit of thinning to the gold plating, probably from sporadic handling and storage in the case. The cylinder does not appear to have been rotated, nor the screws ever turned but there is thinning at the edges, again probably form the case. The markings are clear. Overall, this gun rates in about Excellent condition. 
This pistol comes in a blonde wood Colt Presentation Case, with a Cactus on the front of the case. The case is lined in mustard satin. The fitted case is lined with mustard velvet. There is no key, and the hasp has is functional.
